8663	  The differential-compatibility square in degree \(0\) and in each
8664	  degree \(n+1\) then closes by unfolding the definition of \(\operatorname{augment}\): the
8665	  augmented differentials of \(\Phi(C^\bullet.\operatorname{augment} f)\) and of
8666	  \((\Phi C^\bullet).\operatorname{augment}(\Phi f)\) are literally the same map
